### High Baseline Summary — Additional Families

The following families have High baseline requirements that apply to OpenMRS; full analysis will be documented in the System Security Plan:

| Control Family | Key High Baseline Requirements for OpenMRS |
|---|---|
| Configuration Management (CM) | Automated baseline configuration monitoring; CM-6(1) automated management of configuration settings |
| Risk Assessment (RA) | RA-5 vulnerability scanning at defined frequency; RA-5(1) automated scanning tools |
| System Integrity (SI) | SI-2 flaw remediation with automated patching where possible; SI-3 malicious code protection on endpoints; SI-7 software and firmware integrity verification |
| Personnel Security (PS) | PS-3 personnel screening; PS-4 personnel termination procedures — connects to account deprovisioning |
| Media Protection (MP) | MP-6 media sanitization per NIST SP 800-88; MP-7 media use restrictions |
| Physical Protection (PE) | PE family largely inherited from AWS; MyClinic retains responsibility for workstation physical security |
| Planning (PL) | PL-2 system security plan; PL-4 rules of behavior for system users |
| Program Management (PM) | Enterprise-level requirements; assessed at organizational level |

