## What I Am Still Thinking About

Working through the High baseline today, one area I want to explore more carefully is the CP-7 alternate processing site requirement. For a single-region AWS deployment, meeting this requirement technically requires either a hot standby deployment in a second region (expensive), a warm standby with automated failover capability (moderate cost), or a documented manual procedure for deploying in a second region within the RTO (lower cost, higher recovery time).

For a small clinic with a 4-hour RTO, a warm standby approach — maintaining infrastructure-as-code that can be deployed to a second region and using RDS cross-region snapshots for near-current data — may be the right balance between cost and recovery capability. I want to think through what that architecture looks like and what the cost implications are before the control selection is finalized.

